data.title: TV Premieres: Calendar of Upcoming & Returning Shows
data.meta_description: A calendar of all new and returning shows — streaming, cable, and network.
data.text:
Season 5 Premiere

Tyler Perry’s Assisted Living

After losing his job, Jeremy decides to move to the backwoods of Georgia to help his grandfather, who has purchased a rundown home for the elderly.

Streaming Premiere

Twisters

In an update to the 1996 film, storm chasers find themselves in a fight for their lives as multiple systems converge over Oklahoma.

Streaming Premiere

The Beast Within

Ten-year-old Willow follows her parents on one of their secret late-night treks to the heart of an ancient forest. After witnessing her father undergo a terrible transformation, she too becomes ensnared by the dark ancestral secret that they’ve so desperately tried to conceal.

Movie Premiere

Watchmen: Chapter I

In an alternate world, the murder of a government sponsored superhero draws his outlawed colleagues out of retirement, into a mystery that threatens their lives and the world itself.

New Reality Series

100 Day Hotel Challenge

Brian and Mika Kleinschmidt transform the 1950s Beacon Hotel and William & Garland Motel into charming waterside retreats within a three-month timeline and a $225,000 budget each, with the help of their HGTV all-star team.

Stand-up Special

Matt Rife: Lucid – A Crowd Work Special

Matt gets up close and personal with his audience for a full hour of only crowd work, filmed at The Comedy Zone in Charlotte.

Season 5 Premiere

Expedition Bigfoot

Searchers analyze sightings to pinpoint when and where they are likely to encounter Bigfoot.

New Series

Bad Monkey

Based on the 2013 Carl Hiaasen novel, a former Miami Police Department member turned health inspector investigates a murder mystery while navigating through eccentric characters.

Season 2 Premiere

Star Wars: Young Jedi Adventures

Jedi younglings study the ways of the Force, explore the galaxy, help citizens and creatures in need, and learn valuable skills needed to become Jedi along the way.

Movie Premiere

Daughters

Four young girls prepare for a special Daddy Daughter Dance with their incarcerated fathers, as part of a unique fatherhood program in a Washington, D.C., jail.

Broadcast Premiere

Cult Massacre: One Day in Jonestown

Jim Jones sets out to establish a utopian community in Guyana, but what begins as a peaceful movement ultimately spirals into a mass casualty event that leaves 918 people dead.

Documentary Premiere

Rhythm Masters: A Mickey Hart Experience

Iconic Grateful Dead drummer Mickey Hart creates an original score inspired by conversations with legendary and iconic voices from the world of sports.

Season 4 Premiere

Emily in Paris

A girl from the Midwest is hired to provide an American perspective at a marketing firm in Paris.

Season 3 Premiere

Bel-Air

In a dramatic retelling of The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air, a teenager leaves the streets of West Philadelphia to live with his uncle’s family in Bel-Air.

Season 2 Premiere

Granite Harbour

A police detective with a military past investigates a murder in a Scottish town while confronting his own personal demons and the complexities of a local community fraught with secrets.

Season 2 Premiere

Lost Treasures of Rome

An all-female cast of archeologists make the discovery of a century, find an amphitheater, and search beneath the waves for an ancient resort.

Movie Premiere

Jackpot!

In the near future, a ‘Grand Lottery’ has been newly established in California – the catch: kill the winner before sundown to legally claim their multi-billion dollar jackpot.

Season 18 Premiere

Bering Sea Gold

Four gold dredges and their eccentric crews risk their lives to find as much gold as possible on the bottom of the frigid Bering Sea.

Season 5 Premiere

Cesar Millan: Better Human Better Dog

Cesar Millan gives new pet parents the tools they need to teach their dogs good habits and shed the old bad habits.

Season 4 Premiere

Gold Rush: Mine Rescue with Freddy & Juan

With nearly 40 years of mining under his belt, Freddy Dodge goes on the road to help struggling mine owners to hit the mother lode. He teams up with Juan Ibarra to overhaul washplants, introduce gold recovery techniques, and transform operations.

Season 9 Premiere

Beachfront Bargain Hunt: Renovation

Follows the progress toward purchasing a beachfront fixer upper, which the family then transforms into its very own sun-drenched oasis.

Season 2 Premiere

Side Hustlers

Women entrepreneurs develop their side hustles in the hopes of quitting their day jobs to pursue their dream careers full time.

Movie Premiere

The Union

A down-to-earth construction worker is thrust into the world of super spies and secret agents when his high school sweetheart recruits him on a high-stakes U.S. intelligence mission.

Season 3 Premiere

Chef Swap at the Beach

Hosts head to the beach challenge two local chefs to trade restaurants and cook a meal in each other’s kitchen.

Movie Premiere

Terry McMillan Presents: Tempted By Love

Returning home to care for her aunt, a renowned chef makes an unexpected yet passionate connection with a man who’s 20 years younger than her.

Movie Premiere

A Costa Rican Wedding

A clumsy maid of honor gets help from her handsome nemesis when things go awry at her best friend’s Costa Rican wedding.

New Series

OceanXplorers

Travel aboard the OceanXplorer, OceanX’s state-of-the-art scientific research and exploration vessel, to investigate the farthest frontiers of the world’s oceans, 80% of which are entirely unknown.

New Docuseries

Chimp Crazy

Former nurse-turned-exotic animal broker Tonia Haddix, spends her days caring for animals in captivity, but her limitless love for one chimpanzee in particular spins into a wild cat-and-mouse game with authorities and an animal rights group.

New Reality Series

BBQ High

In a journey across Texas, teens compete in regional BBQ competitions for a shot at the state championship and scholarships. They perfect dishes like dessert, beans, chicken, ribs and brisket while navigating senior year and pivotal life decisions.

Movie Premiere

Trapped in the Rocky Mountains

Lured into an unwelcome reunion at a vacant ski lodge, former college friends find themselves in a fight for their lives when they become the target of an unseen adversary.

Season 3 Premiere

Under the Vines

A mismatched duo inherits a struggling vineyard in New Zealand and must work together to rejuvenate the business while dealing with their personal differences and the quirks of rural life.

Streaming Premiere

Inside Out 2

In a sequel to the 2015 Pixar movie, Joy, Sadness, Anger, Fear and Disgust have been running a successful operation by all accounts. However, when Anxiety shows up, they aren’t sure how to feel.

New Reality Series

Divided By Design

Married designers Ray and Eilyn Jimenez, who run dueling firms, bid against each other for clients in the Miami housing market, and aim to win over potential clients with their distinct design aesthetics.

Streaming Premiere

Oddity

After the brutal murder of her twin sister, Darcy goes after those responsible by using haunted items as her tools for revenge.

New Reality Series

Muslim Matchmaker

Follows Muslim Americans as they navigate cultural customs and showcase the tremendous diversity within the community while looking for modern love.

New Docuseries

Face to Face with Scott Peterson

The man who became infamous in the early 2000s after being convicted of murdering his wife and their unborn son gives his first on-camera comments in more than 20 years.

New Docuseries

Icons Unearthed: Harry Potter

Through a revolving door of directors, an assortment of magical creatures, increasing demand for visual effects, and a cast that is growing up, the Harry Potter series fascinated audiences.

New Series

Wyatt Earp and The Cowboy War

The legendary feud between Wyatt Earp and Ike Clanton unfolds through vivid reenactments of the gunfight that defined an era.

Season 3 Premiere

That ’90s Show

In a spinoff of That ’70s Show, it’s now the summer of 1995, and Leia Forman makes friends with a new generation of Point Place kids.

Season 2 Premiere

Reasonable Doubt

A fearless defense attorney in Los Angeles bucks the justice system and gets judged for her questionable ethics and wild interpretations of the law.

Season 2 Premiere

Avoidance

Newly separated Jonathan has no home, no friends, and no ambition, but is forced to change for the sake of his son.

Movie Premiere

Secret Lives of Orangutans

Following a multi-generational orangutan family through their treetop triumphs and travails in the pristine jungles of Sumatra.

New Series

Unbelievably Vegan With Chef Charity

Celebrity chef Charity Morgan is on a mission to integrate vegan options onto the menu at Nashville's beloved Germantown Pub, a local sports bar run by a stubborn chef who's set in his meat-eating ways.

New Series

Classified

A rebellious teenager is uprooted from her home in Oakland and forced to move in with her estranged father in South Africa.

Season 2 Premiere

Pachinko

The hopes and dreams of four generations of a Korean immigrant family, beginning with a story of a forbidden romance that leads to a sweeping saga taking place in Korea, Japan, and America.

Movie Premiere

The Killer

In a remake of the 1989 action thriller, when a feared contract killer refuses to murder a young blind woman on the orders of her handler, she finds herself hunted by old colleagues and a determined detective.

Movie Premiere

Incoming

Four freshmen in high school get ready for their first school party, they’re preparing themselves for something unfamiliar and terrifying.

Movie Premiere

The Supremes at Earl’s All-You-Can-Eat

Follows a trio of best friends known as "The Supremes" who, for decades, has weathered life's storms together through marriage and children, happiness and blues.

New Series

The Frog

One tranquil summer, a mysterious woman checks into a vacation rental — triggering events that disrupt the lives of the owner and those around him.

Movie Premiere

The Magic of Lemon Drops

When Lolly’s Aunt Gert gives her three magical lemon drops, she gets to experience what her life would have been like if she had made different choices and lived those unfulfilled dreams.

Season 15 Premiere

Evil Lives Here

People tell heart-stopping stories of sharing their homes with loved ones who will become killers.

Season 2 Premiere

Married to Evil

Gripping true stories explore the wickedness behind the wedding and show the devastating consequences of what happens when people are betrayed by those who should love them the most.

New Series

City of God: The Fight Rages On

Set two decades after the events of the movie, Buscapé recounts how conflicts between police, traffickers, and militias impacted the community.

Broadcast Premiere

Deadly DILF

A drunken escapade leads to a one-night stand between college track star Elysium and her married neighbor, Rio. When Rio tries to end their relationship, Elysium’s obsession with him becomes increasingly dangerous.

New Docuseries

The Girl on the Milk Carton

Delves into the story of Jonelle Mathews, who disappeared five days before Christmas in 1984 and became the first missing child given the tragic distinction of appearing on a milk carton.

Season 5 Premiere

The Sommerdahl Murders

A love triangle between Dan Sommerdahl, his wife Marianne and their best friend Flemming occurs as they try to solves killings in Helsingør.

Season 4 Premiere

Only Murders in the Building

Three strangers share an obsession with true crime and suddenly find themselves wrapped up in one.

Streaming Premiere

Kinds of Kindness

Three stories revolve around a man who tries to take control of his own life, a policeman whose wife seems like a different person, and a woman who searches for someone with a special ability.

New Docuseries

Horror’s Greatest

Celebrating the best the genre has to offer, with fresh looks at the classics and scores of hidden gems, plus insights from the masterminds behind your favorite scares.

New Docuseries

Killer Lies: Chasing A True Crime Con Man

Tracking the rise and fall of a provocative French serial killer expert, Stéphane Bourgoin, who built an international reputation with personality quirks and morbid encounters.

Movie Premiere

Untamed Royals

A group of wealthy, privileged youths use their high social status to get away with crimes, but their lavish lifestyle hides a dark truth where the most vulnerable people suffer the consequences of their actions.

Season 2 Premiere

The Lord of the Rings: The Rings of Power

Heroes confront the long-feared reemergence of evil in Middle Earth, carving out legacies that will live on long after they are gone.

New Series

Kaos

A darkly comedic and contemporary reimagining of Greek mythology, exploring themes of gender politics, power, and life in the underworld; six humans learn that they are component parts of an ancient prophecy.

New Series

Terminator Zero

2022: A future war has raged for decades between the few human survivors and an endless army of machines. 1997: The AI known as Skynet gained self-awareness and began its war against humanity.

Movie Premiere

The Deliverance

A family living in a home in Indiana discover strange, demonic occurrences that convince them and the community that the house is a portal to hell.

Season 7 Premiere

90 Day Fiancé: Before the 90 Days

A prequel to 90 Day Fiancé explores the time before the K-1 Visa process starts for Americans who fall in love online.

Season 4 Premiere

The Chosen

Originally a crowd-funded project, retells the life of Jesus Christ and his interactions with his disciples, providing a deep, character-driven backstory to biblical events.

New Series

English Teacher

Evan, a gay high school English teacher, and his coworkers try to balance the demands of the students and their parents.

Premiere

The Chicano Squad

In 1979, Jim Montero and five bilingual Mexican American department rookies were given just 90 days to solve all open Latin murder cases, regain the trust of the community, and assist in any new crimes involving Spanish-speaking people.

Season 3 Premiere

Last One Standing

Comics star in thrilling dramas, but if they’re jokes don’t land during the unscripted scenes, they’re off the show.

New Docuseries

Dark Side of Reality TV

Looks into the origins, real-life impact, and historic moments over decades that have defined the infamous genre of TV.

Movie Premiere

Untold: Hope Solo vs. U.S. Soccer

World Cup champion Hope Solo opens up about her turbulent rise to the top of women's soccer amid public scandals and tension with former teammates.

Season 4 Premiere

Bargain Block

House renovation aces Evan and Keith work around the clock to get their first houses up for sale.

Season 2 Premiere

Tell Me Lies

Lucy Albright and Stephen DeMarco quickly fall into an addictive entanglement that will permanently alter their lives and the lives of everyone around them; a tumultuous and intoxicating relationship unfolds over eight years.

Season 4 Premiere

Slow Horses

Jackson Lamb heads up a team of British intelligence agents who serve in the dumping ground department of MI5 — Slough House — due to their career-ending mistakes.

Live Sports Event

NFL Kickoff

NBC's NFL experts preview the first game of the 2024 NFL season between the Detroit Lions and the Kansas City Chiefs.

New Miniseries

The Perfect Couple

When a lavish wedding ends in disaster before it can even begin — with a body discovered just hours before the ceremony — everyone in the wedding party is a suspect.

New Limited Series

Fight Night: The Million Dollar Heist

On the night of Muhammad Ali’s 1970 comeback fight, a hustler named Chicken Man becomes the prime suspect in the most brazen heist in Atlanta’s history.

Movie Premiere

Apollo 13: Survival

In April 1970, NASA faced the greatest crisis in its history: three astronauts halfway to the moon on a spacecraft that had suffered a catastrophic explosion.

Season 4 Premiere

Power Book II: Ghost

In a sequel to Power, Tariq St. Patrick divides his time between school and hustling to pay for his mum’s defense lawyer.

Movie Premiere

The Thicket

When a bounty hunter and a band of unlikely heroes pursue a brutal killer, they find themselves in a deadly no-man’s-land known as the Thicket.

Movie Premiere

Rebel Ridge

A former Marine confronts corruption in a small town when local law enforcement unjustly seizes the bag of cash he needs to post his cousin’s bail.

New Reality Series

The Secret Lives of Mormon Wives

A group of Mormon mom influencers get caught in the midst of a swinging sex scandal that makes international headlines.

Movie Premiere

The Engagement Plan

Wade's meticulously planned proposal to Kayla goes awry when she changes the plan, leading him to her family's farm where he faces unexpected challenges and her skeptical family.

New Game Show

The Flip Side

Two teams of players attempt to determine the sentiments of two distinct groups regarding the same issue. Teams make their selections from multiple-choice answers, and the correct choice secures the pot.

New Series

Universal Basic Guys

Two brothers lose their jobs to automation and are given $3,000 a month in a new basic income program, allowing them to use their free time and free money to find purpose in a world where they’re no longer needed.

Season 4 Premiere

My Brilliant Friend

Set in a gritty Naples neighborhood, two very different girls from the top of their class struggle from childhood to adulthood, against a backdrop of socio-political change and personal turmoil.

Season Premiere

Texas Country Reporter

Host Bob Phillips explores the back roads of Texas to discover unique travel stops and meet ordinary people with extraordinary stories.

Special

Presidential Debate

In the second in-person showdown of the 2024 election cycle, Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump face off.

Season 2 Premiere

The Old Man

A former CIA operative learns that to ensure his future he must reconcile his past.

New Series

Three Women

Writer Gia convinces three women to tell her their stories; entrepreneur Sloane, homemaker Lina and student Maggie are on a crash course to radically overturn their lives.

New Series

How To Die Alone

After a comical brush with death, a Black neurotic woman refuses to settle for anything less than the life she wants.

Movie Premiere

LEGO Star Wars: Rebuild the Galaxy

A nerf-herder discovers an artifact that swaps the roles of heroes and villains in the Star Wars universe, prompting him to embark on an adventure to restore order and reassemble the fractured galaxy.

Movie Premiere

Uglies

In a futuristic dystopia with enforced beauty standards, a teen awaiting mandatory cosmetic surgery embarks on a journey to find her missing friend.

New Series

In Vogue: The 90s

The definitive story of the fashion industry in the 90s — Hollywood, Grunge, The Met Gala — through the eyes of Vogue editors.

Season 19 Premiere

Sister Wives

Follows Kody Brown, his four wives, and their combined 18 children trying to live as a “normal” family in a society that shuns their lifestyle.

Season 2 Premiere

Tulsa King

New York mafia capo Dwight “The General” Manfredi faces the startling task of reestablishing his Italian mafia family after serving 25 years in prison.

Season 2 Premiere

Ridley

Retired Detective Inspector Alex Ridley is enlisted by his former protégée, DI Carol Farman, to consult on a missing person case which takes a dark and unexpected turn.

New Series

Moonflower Murders

Editor Susan Ryeland is tasked with finding the solution to a real-life cold case hidden within one of Alan Conway’s early Atticus Pünd novels.

Movie Premiere

Nightmare in the Desert

After returning to her childhood home outside Joshua Tree National Park, an outdoor enthusiast and her urbanite boyfriend are secretly tracked through the desert by a mysterious figure hellbent on preventing the boyfriend’s surprise proposal — even if it means murder.

Season 28 Premiere

Antiques Roadshow

Collectors discover that they can turn trash into treasure, thanks to the appraisal skills of the show’s specialists in antiques and fine art.

New Series

High Potential

A single mom with three kids, an exceptional mind, and unconventional knack for solving crime leads to a partnership with a by-the-book seasoned detective.

Movie Premiere

Child Star

Explores growing up in the spotlight through the lens of some of the world’s most famous former child stars.

Season 47 Premiere

Survivor

Castaways inhabit a remote destination and attempt to outwit, outlast and outplay each other for a prize of $1 million.

New Series

Agatha All Along

Set after the events of WandaVision, Agatha Harkness recruits some unlikely allies on her quest to regain her former powers.

Season 2 Premiere

The Golden Bachelorette

In a sequel to The Golden Bachelor, one hopeless romantic is given a second chance at love in the search for a partner with whom to share the sunset years of life.

New Series

The Penguin

In a spinoff of The Batman, the transformation of Oswald Cobblepot from a disfigured nobody to a noted Gotham gangster.

New Series

The Queen of Villains

Based upon the life of Dump Matsumoto, a professional wrestler who rose to prominence in All Japan Women's Pro-Wrestling in the 1980s.

Season 2 Premiere

Frasier

Dr. Frasier Crane is off to a different city with new challenges to face, new relationships to forge, and an old dream or two to finally fulfill.

New Series

Twilight of the Gods

Sigrid, an iron-willed warrior, saves Leif, a mortal king, who falls in love with her. They both survive Thor’s wrath of terror which embarks them and a crew of crusaders on a merciless mission for vengeance, against all odds.

New Reality Series

La Maison

High fashion meets high drama at a French haute couture house. When the family dynasty behind the house falls into scandal, they must find a way to reinvent themselves or be destroyed by their rivals.

Movie Premiere

Omni Loop

A quantum physicist finds herself stuck in a time loop with a black hole growing in her chest and only a week to live. When she meets a gifted student they team up to save her life and unlock the mysteries of time travel.

Movie Premiere

Falling Together

Natalie tries to bring feuding neighbors together in her new condo building. Her unexpected ally is the building’s super who prefers to avoid getting involved.

Season 3 Premiere

From

The residents of a small town are trapped by an invisible barrier and must survive mysterious threats while uncovering why they can’t leave.

New Series

Matlock

In a reboot of the classic show, Septuagenarian Madeline “Matty” Matlock decides to rejoin the workforce at a prestigious law firm where she uses her unassuming demeanor and wily tactics to win cases and expose corruption from within.

New Series

Rescue: HI-Surf

An action-packed drama that follows the personal and professional lives of the heavy-water lifeguards who patrol and protect the North Shore of O’ahu — the most famous and dangerous stretch of coastline in the world.

Season 5 Premiere

9-1-1: Lone Star

A New York firefighter, who was the lone survivor of his Manhattan firehouse on 9/11, relocates to Austin, with his son, where he works to save people’s lives while trying to solve his own personal problems.

New Series

Murder in a Small Town

Karl Alberg moves to a quiet coastal town to escape police work only to find himself solving murders there.

New Series

Penelope

A 16-year-old girl abruptly leaves her family and the comforts of life behind after developing an almost cosmic-like attraction to the wilderness.

Season 12 Premiere

The Masked Singer

Celebrities compete against one another while shrouded from head to toe in an elaborate costume.

Season 2 Premiere

The Floor

A trivia battle in which 81 contestants stand on 81 squares on a massive game show floor, competing for a whopping grand prize.

New Series

Grotesquerie

A series of crimes have unsettled a small community, and Detective Lois Tryon feels they are eerily personal, as if someone or something is taunting her.

Movie Premiere

Fly

Over seven years, three couples involved in the extreme sport of BASE jumping test the limits of love and life itself. Risking everything for the thrill of the jump, their dedication is put to the ultimate test.

Season 8 Premiere

9-1-1

Emergency response must try to balance saving those who are at their most vulnerable with solving the problems in their own lives

Season 21 Premiere

Grey’s Anatomy

A group of surgical interns and their mentors at a hospital in Seattle try to balance complex relationships and challenging cases.

Season 3 Premiere

Crime Scene Kitchen

To take home a $100,000 prize, bakers must decode what type of dessert was made using just crumbs and a few elusive clues.

Season 2 Premiere

Colin From Accounts

Ashley and Gordon are brought together by a car accident and an injured dog, and learn to navigate life together while showing their true selves, scars and all.

New Series

Doctor Odyssey

Max is the new on-board doctor for a luxury cruise ship where the small but mighty medical team navigate unique medical crises and each other, miles from shore.

Movie Premiere

Apartment 7A

In a prequel to Rosemary’s Baby, when a struggling, young dancer suffers a devastating injury, she finds herself drawn in by dark forces when a peculiar, well-connected, older couple promises her a shot at fame.

New Docuseries

Social Studies

A social experiment, filmed in Los Angeles over a school year, features a diverse group of LA teens who open up their lives and phones to offer an intimate glimpse into how social media has reshaped childhood.

Movie Premiere

Rez Ball

The Chuska Warriors, a Native American high school basketball team from New Mexico, must band together after losing their star player if they want to keep their quest for a state championship alive.

Movie Premiere

She Taught Love

A guy, Frank, on a self-destructive path. A girl, Mali, with an expiration date. What a perfect time to meet and fall in love.

Movie Premiere

He Slid Into Her DMs

Berni is a 17-year-old social media influencer who agrees to sell private photos to an online fan named Mason. However, things take a deadly turn when Mason shows up on her doorstep, causing her mom to make a tragic decision.

Season 2 Premiere

Krapopolis

A flawed family of humans, gods and monsters must run an ancient city without killing each other.

Season 2 Premiere

The Walking Dead: Daryl Dixon

Following his departure from The Commonwealth, Daryl Dixon washes ashore in France, raising the ire of a splintered but growing autocratic movement centered in Paris and endangering a young boy at the heart of a benevolent religious movement.

New Reality Series

The Summit

Sixteen strangers embark on a once-in-a-lifetime journey through the treacherous New Zealand Alps in an attempt to reach the peak of a distant, towering mountain.

Season Premiere

WWE NXT

WWE’s next generation of superstars battle to make an impact on their rise to fame.

Season 2 Premiere

Accused

Based upon the British series, stories of defendants in criminal trials reveal how one wrong turn leads to another, until it’s too late to turn back.

New Series

Joan

The fiery and uncompromising Joan Hannington becomes a master jewel thief in a bid to create a secure home for her daughter.

Season 2 Premiere

Big Freedia Means Business

Big Freedia navigates various business opportunities that have come her way in the last few years.

Season 2 Premiere

Sullivan’s Crossing

Neurosurgeon Maggie Sullivan reconnects with her small-town past after a scandal causes her to leave her professional and personal life behind in the city.

New Series

Where’s Wanda?

In search of their missing daughter, a couple disguises themselves as employees of an electrical company, bug their neighborhood, and find out that behind closed doors, none of their neighbors are who they pretend to be.

New Series

Last Days of the Space Age

Set in 1979 Western Australia. A power strike threatens to plunge the region into darkness, while the city hosts the iconic Miss Universe pageant and the US space station, Skylab, crashes just beyond the city's suburbs.

New Limited Series

The Last Days of the Space Age

Set in 1979 Western Australia. A power strike threatens to plunge the region into darkness, while the city hosts the iconic Miss Universe pageant and the US space station, Skylab, crashes just beyond the city's suburbs.

Season 3 Premiere

Heartstopper

Based on the graphic novel series, teens Charlie and Nick discover their unlikely friendship might be something more.

Season 3 Premiere

The Legend of Vox Machina

Vox Machina, a band of eight unlikely heroes, find themselves on a quest to save the realm of Exandria from dark magical forces.

Season 2 Premiere

Found

A recovery specialist and her team stop at nothing to find missing people because for them, it’s personal — every member of the team has firsthand experience with a mysterious disappearance.

Movie Premiere

Hold Your Breath

In 1930s Oklahoma amid the region's horrific dust storms, a woman is convinced that a sinister presence is threatening her family.

Season 7 Premiere

Press Your Luck

Three contestants compete against one another in a game of wits and strategy, answering questions to earn spins on the Big Board.

New Game Show

Trivial Pursuit

The iconic game is reimagined on a giant version of the iconic game board, as contestants battle it out over a range of play-along question categories to win wedges and beat each other to the center.

New Game Show

Scrabble

Wordsmiths battle it out playing a series of addictive, word-based games to win points and add words to a giant Scrabble board in the center of the set.

New Docuseries

Citizen Nation

Teenagers from across America with diverse personal and political backgrounds come together to compete in the nation’s premier civics competition, “We the People.”

New Docuseries

Scamanda

Wife, mother and blogger Amanda Riley’s tragic cancer tale captivates thousands, but after an anonymous tip to an investigative reporter, her own words may prove to be her downfall.

New Series

Teacup

In an adaptation of the Robert R. McCammon novel, a mysterious danger menaces strangers at a Texas ranch, forcing them to unite against the unknown threat.

New Series

Citadel: Diana

In the Italian chapter of the Citadel universe set in 2030 Milan, an undercover Citadel agent, trapped behind enemy lines within the enemy syndicate Manticore, must trust an unexpected ally to escape and disappear forever.

New Series

Disclaimer

When a novel appears at the bedside of a journalist whose career has been built on revealing transgressions, she realizes she’s a key character in a long-buried story-one that exposes her dark secret.

Season 2 Premiere

Tracker

Lone-wolf survivalist Colter Shaw roams the country as a reward seeker, using his expert tracking skills to help private citizens and law enforcement solve all manner of mysteries while contending with his own fractured family.

Season 4 Premiere

FBI: International

The FBI’s International Fly Team tracks and neutralizes threats against American citizens.

Season 2 Premiere

Shrinking

A grieving therapist starts to break the rules by telling his clients exactly what he thinks.

New Series

Nemesis

A Dutch prosecutor and detective investigate financial crimes among wealthy elites. As the cases blur work and life, she must trust her instincts to uncover a conspiracy protecting ill-gotten fortunes at all costs.

New Game Show

Are You Smarter Than a Celebrity?

An adult contestant joins a classroom of celebrities to answer elementary-level questions across various topics, vying for a $100,000 prize.

Season 4 Premiere

Superman & Lois

Clark Kent and Lois Lane face their greatest challenge — being working parents in today’s society.

Season 4 Premiere

Ghosts

A couple learn the estate they are converting into a bed and breakfast is inhabited by spirits.

Season 2 Premiere

Jurassic World: Chaos Theory

Set after the events at Camp Cretaceous, members of The Nublar Six struggle to find their footing off the islands, navigating a world filled with dinosaurs and people who want to hurt them.

New Series

Georgie & Mandy’s First Marriage

In a spinoff of Young Sheldon, Georgie and Mandy raise their young family in Texas while navigating the challenges of adulthood, parenting, and marriage.

Movie Premiere

Brothers

Two criminal twin brothers, one trying to reform, embark on a dangerous heist road trip.

Season 16 Premiere

Shark Tank

Millionaires receive business proposals from entrepreneurs and decide whether to make an investment.

Midseason Premiere

Blue Bloods

A multigenerational family of police officers dedicated to enforcing the law in New York.

Season 8 Premiere

S.W.A.T.

A Los Angeles S.W.A.T. lieutenant balances loyalty to the job and to the streets where he grew up.

Season 3 Premiere

Lopez vs Lopez

A working-class family comedy about dysfunction, reconnection, and all the pain and joy in between.

Season 3 Premiere

Fire Country

Bode Donovan and other inmates joins a firefighting program looking for redemption and a shortened prison sentence.

New Series

Hysteria!

A struggling high school heavy metal band of outcasts use the town's sudden interest in the occult to start a reputation as a Satanic metal band, until a strange series of events triggers a witch hunt that leads back to them.
